      "element_id": "slide_79_Title_3",
      "source_text": "Governance Mechanisms",
      "character_count": 21,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": false,
      "layout_context": "Shape: Title 3",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-050",
      "slide_or_page": 79,
      "element_type": "text_box",
      "element_id": "slide_79_Text_Placeholder_3",
      "source_text": "A strong internal control environment\nCodes of ethical conduct\nFair, ethical, transparent and consistently applied procedures\nBudgeting, control and monitoring of procurement spend\nClearly defined roles, responsibilities, accountabilities and reporting structures\nControls over the authority levels of individual buyers\nClear requirements for approvals and authorisations\nClear audit trails\nThe segregation of procurement duties",
      "character_count": 428,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": false,
      "layout_context": "Shape: Text Placeholder 3",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-051",
      "slide_or_page": 80,
      "element_type": "slide_title",
      "element_id": "slide_80_Title_3",
      "source_text": "Security in Data",
      "character_count": 16,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": false,
      "layout_context": "Shape: Title 3",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
      "flag_options": null,
      "expansion_risk": null
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "SEG-052",
      "slide_or_page": 80,
      "element_type": "text_box",
      "element_id": "slide_80_Text_Placeholder_3",
      "source_text": "Consideration must be given to ensuring data security is appropriate and considers;\nPhysical risks e.g. controlling who has access to your buildings and how much of the building they can access, when and where deliveries are made\nPersonnel risks (ensuring people are who they say they are, contractors manage sub-contractors effectively and identify possible motives to compromise your information)\nCyber risks (do suppliers hold sensitive information on secure networks?)",
      "character_count": 472,
      "is_in_text_box": true,
      "is_in_table": false,
      "layout_context": "Shape: Text Placeholder 3",
      "translation_status": "PENDING",
      "translated_text": null,
      "flag_status": null,
